<br>
Besides, this is all relatively worthless as far as an argument goes.  If you want to validate or negate the value of Torpor, go to the Shaman's Crucible and ask for opinions there.  <br>
<br>
The basis of this thread, and 99% of all the other "druids need help" threads on this board can almost all be traced back to one simple fact:  We have no set role in raids.<br>
<br>
I think one of the largest reasons that this still remains true today is because the actual Druid Community can't even figure out where it wants to end up.  40% of us want to be the premier secondary healers, 40% of us want to be the premier secondary nukers, and 20% of us want to have misc tasks like debuffs or tank buffs.  All in all, what that says is that the Druid Community has a "Swiss Army Knife" mentality.<br>
<br>
The short version is that we're not going to get upgrades to everything.  The one deciding push that got druids the healing changes that they have now (and most likely the change to moonfire) is that the same opinions were voiced uniformly by 98% of the druid population.  Right now other than a generic, "We can't do anything" attitude, there's no solid rallying cry.  <br>
<br>
Since no one can even seem to generate a topic that even 90% of the community can agree on, what that tells me is that the druid is an average class that is not "broken."  Therefore I doubt the need for the expedience for the "fix us before everyone" cry that's been voiced so much recently. <p><body link="#FFFFFF" vlink="#CCCCCC">

