<br>
It's also dependent on what you define as a major raid as well.  I don't consinder AL/Creator/THO rhag 1 or rhag 2 major raids anymore.  Hell even the Blood of Ssra, isn't that tuff.<br>
<br>
------Enough about clerics.<br>
<br>
As far as being a druid in the high end scene, druids can contribute a lot.  A smart druid isn't going to be nuking like a wizard till oom, that druid will find a balance between nuking and healing their group.<br>
<br>
In long duration fights like the Cursed for example, 1 druid can dish out about 70-80k in DoT damage in a period of 20 minutes.  Granted a necromancer can deal about 160k in DoT damage in the same period of time, but 80k for one druid, that's not shabby at all.  With my mana regen, I'm always fm by the time I need to refresh WD or Breath of Ro.  I can even throw in a moonfire between rounds with the extend affliction focus item, adding about another 15k in damage without going below 80m.  Add in Mind wrack I can nuke twice as much more, and maintain dotting and still maintain 80m.  <br>
Spread the dots around, 2-3 druids can average 60k of damage this fight.  Add in the amount of healing mana I have left to assist heal as needed, I'm golden.<br>
<br>
If your not finding the role you want in a guild, blame yourself or the guild for that.  Granted there are a few tweaks here and there, but a druid can offer so much more then what many of you are saying we don't offer.  <br>
<br>
Your only as useful as you believe yourself to be, and I'm damn more useful then a cleric that just clicks a button after counting a few seconds and my guild knows it.  A trained monkey can do that.  <br>
<br>
At the start of the Druid petition we had here I agreed with a lot of the things, but now, I don't agree with many of the things we wanted.<br>
<br>
Just like many necromancers attitudes that all they are there for are to corpse summon and mana feed.  Heh, none of our necromancers mana feed on a raid aside from Mindwracking.  Our necromancers know they can do a lot more to contribute to a raid then just mana feed.  They can heal, they can deal damage.   <p><a href=http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=142925>~Aerillea Mystfyre~</a>
