The only advantage a level 52 cleric has over a 60 druid in a healing situation is CH.  But if your melees are that stupid to be taking riposte damage consistently, then CH is obviously needed.   The only time melees in my guild other then the main tank takes damage are from those silly curses and ae's in Luclin.<br>
<br>
Using a combination of Winged Death, Breath of Ro, Drones of Doom from Bracer, and Choking Spores on a engaged or rooted mob, my dot damage is around, lets see:<br>
<br>
Breath of Ro: 920, 11 ticks<br>
Winged Death: 1287, 10 ticks<br>
Drones of Doom: 340 pts, 11 ticks<br>
Choking Spores: 450 pts, 10 ticks<br>
<br>
Total: 2997<br>
Apply 12% root/engagement bonus: = 3356<br>
Duration ticks = 10.5<br>
Result = 319/Tick<br>
DPS = 53.26<br>
<br>
Apply Focus items, Extend Affliction and Affliction Efficiency, add 15% over those totals, we get:<br>
<br>
Result = 367/Tick<br>
DPS = 61 <br>
<br>
Give or take tick differentials with stacking times.<br>
<br>
20 Minutes = 200Ticks<br>
200 x 367 = 73,400<br>
<br>
With bard song I can continously keep this up.  Over with 1 druid versus 1 wizard, in lets say a 40 minute battle, that one druids DPS is larger then 1 wizard who will have to either med to regain mana or use click robes to continus his dps.<br>
<br>
