<br>
<br>
Wrong.  Go look at the DoT testing results thread in the Archive, do your own testing, and come back.<br>
<br>
You're even wrong about the penalty, by the way.  It's a 33% penalty.  Sheesh. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#f7f5e6><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub13.ezboard.com/utalyenatrueheart.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Talyena Trueheart</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br> <font color=#333399>(6/19/02 5:17:06 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub13.ezboard.com/fthedruidsgrovegeneral.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=27643.topic&index=57>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Stop complaining</span><hr size=1> How many druids usually are at your raids? Take all away but one and see if your guild can still do the raid. Assuming a good cleric turnout, I am sure you not being there won't effect them one bit. Now lets assume you need a six cleric rotation and only five clerics show up. That one missing ch rotation cleric can bring the raid to a halt. You can do a raid with one druid (or even none), but you cant do it without ch rotation clerics.<br>
<br>
Sorry you think I am an idiot, but warriors in 99% of the cases fight from the front of the mob. If not and the first warrior goes down, the mob will spin around and hit everyone with riposte damage. It will also lower every melee's dps until you get the mob turned back around. Also, in many cases, the warrior will be out of ch range if they are behind the target. That guarentees that many melee will die and quite possibly a raid failure due to the lack of a proper switch. Then there are non rooted mobs. How do you think you can control mob positioning if everyone is behind the mob? Once again it is the warriors who have to take up the slack in front of the mob so that the rogues can do their thing from the back. So, you see, warriors aren't stupid for taking riposte damage, sometimes they have to do it in order to insure the success of the raid (and I bet you thought they hit attack and went outside for a smoke break).<br>
<br>
You made a nice dot list, and if a druid had all the proper equipment then they might have a decent dps (still not that high though). But once again, a single druid can do it. There is no stackability with dots, so no reason to bring more than one druid other than nuking or healing. As for wizards, they can sit to regen mana, or they can stand there with kei, ft items, and bard song working while they maintain a steady 40+ dps with items like the robe off of velketor. <p><font size="+1"><i><font face="Georgia, Times New Roman, Times, serif" size="-1"><b><a href=http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=153420>Talyena Trueheart</a>, Hierophant of Tunare<br><a href=http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=203026>Tresha Trueheart</a>, Warlord for Erollisi Marr<br>Dawntreaders, Terris-Thule</b></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#e6ebd7><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub13.ezboard.com/ustormhaven.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Stormhaven</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>FAQ/Index Moderator</span><br> <font color=#333399>(6/19/02 5:20:55 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub13.ezboard.com/fthedruidsgrovegeneral.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=27643.topic&index=58>Reply</a>   <BR><img src=http://web2.airmail.net/naomi/amalgam/forum/stormhaven.gif WIDTH=60 HEIGHT=60></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Stop complaining</span><hr size=1> <i>I believe I am more useful then a standard CH rotation cleric. I'm sorry, it doesn't take much more then a bot to maintain a CH rotation.</i><br>
<br>
This can be negated by saying the following:<br>
If you have no clerics, you have no raid.<br>
If you have no druids, you still have a raid.<br>
<br>
It doesn't matter how useful you feel in a raid - you may be the raid organizer, the group god, the loot distributor, the tactical advisor.  That's all about you and what you do for your raid/guild.  The question at hand is how useful is a druid at a raid event.  Usually, the answer is that druids are nice to have around, but we are by no means needed or necessary.  Whether a cleric can be replaced by a bot or a script is irrelevant, the fact is that they are required in order for the raid to take place.<br>
<br>
<i>The only advantage a level 52 cleric has over a 60 druid in a healing situation is CH. </i><br>
<br>
Ok, but that's a hell of an advantage.  That's almost like saying someone standing 100 miles away with a nuclear warhead doesn't have much of an advantage versus another person standing on an open street with a 9mm.<br>
<br>
<i>The only time melees in my guild other then the main tank takes damage are from those silly curses and ae's in Luclin.</i><br>
<br>
Your guild not fight many mobs with Rampage?<br>
Even with a well sorted tanking order, rampage's hate list is dynamic and changes from moment to moment (as people step outside of the range, aggro is increased, etc).  A tank taking two rampages can easily have their total hp cut in half (or worse).  A well timed CB can be the difference between that tank living or dipping into the "low hp" aggro zone and getting eaten.<br>
<br>
<i>Over with 1 druid versus 1 wizard, in lets say a 40 minute battle, that one druids [DOT] DPS is larger then 1 wizard who will have to either med to regain mana or use click robes to continus his dps.</i><br>
<br>
Couple of things - <br>
In order to get an accurate dps read out for DoTs, you'd have to do quite a few tests in order to get a meaningful number.  The dps you've got calculated there are best case scenarios - no fizzles, no resists.  I've found that counting on BoR for any amount of dps is pretty iffy due to it's high resist and fizzle factor.  If you're using DoD from an armor piece, that's 10s for casting, so you've got about 30s to sit and med in that scenario.  Now, I'm sure this is guild/server specific, but we don't have many high level bards on our server, so getting AE manasong is not an assured thing.  Usually there's one bard, and more than likely, he's in the damage shield group.  What's your mana usage look like if you keep that up in the Cursed fight, or any other 30+ min fight, without a bard?  <br>
<br>
I'm also assuming that you're having someone else debuff fire (or you're running in and debuffing, then waiting to lose aggro).  I know BoR doesn't like sticking on 90% of the Luclin mobs without Smolder/Sunder (even with malo already on).  <br>
<br>
Second - you're dps of the wizards is a bit flawed.  First off, in a raid if you're DoT'ing using all four of those DoTs, you've just bumped up your own personal dps.  However, what are you having the other druids doing?  Moonfire/Wildfire?  Compare the average dps of four wizards versus four druids in the same situation.<br>
<br>
Everyone needs to remember that when calculating dps on spells, you can't just go by what the spellbook says you can do.  Resists are a very big factor.  Tanks can calculate their dps by running their logs through parsers - they can see that they did from 0 to 300+ damage on hits, and average that out.  You cannot assume that moonfire will always do 1150 to a target and say that your dps is XX_amount based on that calculation. <p><body link="#FFFFFF" vlink="#CCCCCC">

